Where appropriate to the class of patient conveyed, passenger cars may be used subject to these being:  Minimum of 4 doors all of which are to be in good working condition  Body style; saloon car or medium sized hatchback  Unmodified from manufacturer’s standard specification.

Body style means a level of commonality in vehicle construction as defined by number of doors and roof treatment (e.g., sedan, convertible, fastback, hatchback) and number of seats (i.e., front, second, or third seat) requiring seat belts pursuant to National Highway Traffic Safety Administration safety regulations in 49 CFR part 571.
